# Conspiracy Theory Forum

Mystery-first discussion board featuring a React + TypeScript + Tailwind frontend and a Spring Boot GraphQL backend.

## Backend
- Location: `backend/`
- Framework: Spring Boot (Java 21) + Spring GraphQL
- Start: `mvn spring-boot:run`
- GraphiQL console: `http://localhost:8080/graphiql` (path `/graphql`)

## Frontend
- Location: `frontend/`
- Framework: React + Vite + Apollo Client + Tailwind
- Start: `npm run dev` (defaults to `http://localhost:5173`)
- Set `VITE_GRAPHQL_URL` to point at the backend GraphQL endpoint when not using the default `http://localhost:8080/graphql`.

## Features
- Paginated theory feed with status / keyword filters and hot-sorting by comment activity.
- Login via shared "secret code" to post or comment (anonymous option included).
- Theory creation supports evidence URLs and status tagging.
- Detailed side panel shows comments and allows new posts once logged in.

## Notes
Package downloads from remote registries may require network access. If installs fail, configure registry/proxy access as needed.
